node.text:
New Zealand Mountain roads .. 

Who else loves them?

These were shot with my @tamronnz 70-200mm lens. Its pretty amazing the compression a zoom lens can give and make them big ol mountains look even more amazing. 

Thanks @iamtheflyingkiwi for helping with Shots 1 and 2

#tamronnz #nzmustdo #newzealandvacations #newzealandguide #thisisliving #bestnz #purenewzealand #nz #hellofrom #newzealand #destinationnz #purenz

node.text:
When your winter wonderland dreams come true ❄️ 

A couple of days ago @iamtheflyingkiwi and I drove into Milford Sound without knowing a snow storm was forecast. We had checked our weather apps and it seemed like pretty a good forecast so off we went. We thought it was weird that the road was closing over night but still didn’t click! 

During the night we heard snow on our roof and by the next morning we woke up to an absolute winter wonderland (2nd shot). We drove as far as we could until the road reopened and then this was the scene waiting for us (1st shot).

Absolute dreams and feel very lucky to have witnessed such a magical scene. We stayed here for hours taking it all in, chatting to Kea parrots and tomtits .. freezing our butts off. Lots to come from this day.. still on the road however. 

Check out my story highlights for more 😍

node.text:
Strolling across Mars at sunset .. except Mars was an epic landscape in @northlandnz New Zealand that really doesn’t get enough attention!

After a lifetime (well .. my lifetime) of wanting to visit the Te Paki sand dunes, I finally made it and it was just as beautiful as I had imagined it would be.

Some of the dunes can reach up to 100 metres from over 1 million years of volcanic sand build up. 

@iamtheflyingkiwi and I set off on an amazing (and hectic) road trip last week that saw us cover a record amount of driving to get to the top of New Zealand in the shortest space of time .. we are crazy 😝 but it was so worth it. 

I totally recommend taking the trip up here .. check out my story highlight for more.

Unfortunately the Instagram crop didn’t help me much with the second shot as it was composed as a landscape. 

Have a great weekend everyone ✌️

I photographed this spot on a road trip we took exploring the North Island and as always I took my @lexarmemory SL200 Portable SSD to back up my files. The SL200 is the perfect travel SSD being super slim and fast transfer speeds.

The fires on .. come on in ⛄️ 

With the South Island being transformed into a winter wonderland this week, how good would it be to have a little cabin like this in the mountains to escape to ! 

Here are a few shots with the chilly white stuff that make my toes numb just thinking about it . In saying that I can’t wait to get down there next month a good ol winter roadie adventure.

Shots are: 
1. Mackenzie Basin - shot on @tamronnz 70-200 G2 lens
2. Roy’s Peak Wanaka 
3. Hakatere Conservation Reserve
4. Roy’s Peak Wanaka 
5. Hooker River Mount Cook
